<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-656-688  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 656 688.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  July 23 1990 v36 n1819 p14(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Byrd (Amendment) watching. (amendment to 1990 DefenseAuthorization Act) (Government Closeup) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sen Robert Byrd's amendment to the FY 1990 Defense AuthorizationAct, which made it a criminal offense to use money from governmentcontracts to influence other government offices to win othercontracts, has failed abysmally.andP;  Some big defense contracts cutoff third-party contacts, affecting hundreds of innocentconsultants and technical support contractors.andP;  But others havestood their ground and continued business as usual while waitingfor the issues to be clarified.andP;  The Office of Management andBudget has, belatedly, set forth guidelines for administering theByrd Amendment.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Statute:   Defense Authorization Act of 1989 (amendments).andO;Topic:     LegislationDefense contractsUnited States. Office of Management and BudgetGovernment Regulation.andO;Person:    Byrd, Robert C. (political activity).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>